---
description: Flutter (Dart) client conventions for apps/timemanager.
globs: apps/timemanager/**
---

`apps/timemanager` is the Flutter (Dart) client. Package manager is **Flutter/Dart** via `pubspec.yaml` — never pnpm/npm/Deno here.

Source layout (`lib/`):

- `config/api_config.dart` — GraphQL (`:3000`) and SuperTokens auth API (`:3001`) endpoints.
- `l10n/` — ARB templates (`app_en.arb`, `app_es.arb`, …) and generated `AppLocalizations` (via `flutter gen-l10n` / `l10n.yaml`). Put all user-facing copy in ARB; do not hardcode UI strings in widgets.
- `models/` — data models (e.g. `activity.dart`).
- `router/` — `go_router` config (`app_router.dart`, `app_routes.dart`, `auth_controller.dart`). Browser path syncs to shell tabs (`/overview`, `/activities`, `/calendar`) plus `/login`, `/groups`, `/settings`.
- `screens/` — UI screens (`login_screen.dart`, `activities_screen.dart`, `activity_form_screen.dart`).
- `services/` — `auth_service.dart` (SuperTokens FDI + header tokens), `graphql_client.dart` (Bearer GraphQL), repositories.
- `theme/` — app-only theme helpers (e.g. `calendar_view` merge via `withCalendarTheme`).
- `widgets/` — domain UI helpers. Shared design-system widgets come from `package:design_system` (`libs/design_system`).

Auth: email/password + OAuth against `user-manager-api`. Tokens are stored via `shared_preferences` and sent as `Authorization: Bearer` (header mode). The official `supertokens_flutter` package is Android/iOS-only; this app targets Chrome, so FDI is called directly. `AuthController` bootstraps the session (including OAuth query params) and drives router redirects.

Dev workflow: `pnpm timemanager` starts the API stack only; launch the Flutter client from the IDE (**Run and Debug → timemanager**, Chrome `:4444`, hot reload on save). CLI alternatives: `nx serve timemanager` (`flutter run -d chrome --web-port=4444`; also starts `user-manager-api`), `nx test timemanager`, `nx run timemanager:analyze`, `nx run timemanager:pub-get`.

Cloud APIs: `DOMAIN=… nx run timemanager:build-web|build-macos|build-ios|build-ipa|build-apk|build-appbundle|build-linux|build-windows` / `serve-cloud`, or IDE **timemanager (cloud)** / **(macos, cloud)** with `config/cloud.dart-defines.json` (see `.ai/workflows.md`).

Do not edit generated/platform output: `build/`, `.dart_tool/`, `android/`, `ios/`, `linux/`, `macos/`, `windows/` (unless a change genuinely requires touching a platform folder). Generated l10n Dart under `lib/l10n/app_localizations*.dart` is produced by `flutter gen-l10n` — edit `app_en.arb` / `l10n.yaml`, not the generated files by hand.
